Column Comment.0: APPLICATION ID: The unique identifier for the application that the attachments arepart of.
Column Comment.1: ATTACHMENT ID: Unique identifier for the attachment for the application
Column Comment.2: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.3: ATTACHMENT DESCRIPTION: Describes physical attachments to the submissions,such as maps, reports etc.
Column Comment.4: ATTACHMENT TYPE: The type of attachment, such as map, report, letter etc.
Column Comment.5: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.6: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.7: PHYSICAL ITEM ID: The unique identifier for the physical item that represents thecontents of this attachment.
Column Comment.8: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.9: RECEIVED DATE: the date that an attachment was received.
Column Comment.10: RECEIVED INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating that an attachment has been received.
Column Comment.11: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.12: SENT BY: The business associate who sent this attachment to the recipient.
Column Comment.13: SENT DATE: The date that the attachment to the application was sent.
Column Comment.14: SENT INDICATOR: a Y/N flag indicating that this attachment was sent.
Column Comment.15: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.16: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.17: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.18: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.19: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.20: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.21: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.22: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
